  "prompt": "How can your remove white underarm stains from shirts?",
  "response": "Here are several methods to remove white underarm stains from shirts:\n\n1. White vinegar and water solution\n- Mix equal parts white vinegar and water\n- Apply directly to the stain\n- Let sit for 30 minutes\n- Wash normally\n\n2. Baking soda paste\n- Mix baking soda with water to create a paste\n- Apply to stain\n- Gently scrub\n- Let sit for 20 minutes\n- Wash normally\n\n3. Hydrogen peroxide and dish soap\n- Mix equal parts hydrogen peroxide and dish soap\n- Apply to stain\n- Let sit for 1 hour\n- Wash normally\n\n4. Aspirin solution\n- Crush 2-3 aspirin tablets\n- Mix with water to create a paste\n- Apply to stain\n- Let sit for 1 hour\n- Wash normally\n\n5. Commercial stain removers\n- Use specialized underarm stain removal products\n- Follow package instructions\n\n6. Prevention tips\n- Use antiperspirant instead of deodorant\n- Allow deodorant to dry before dressing\n- Wear undershirts to protect clothing\n\nAlways check garment care labels and test a small, inconspicuous area first to ensure the method won't damage the fabric.",
